==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Jongler
<hw>Jon"gler</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
}</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>jongleur</ets>. See
<er>Juggler</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>In the Middle Ages, a court attendant or other
person who, for hire, recited or sang verses, usually of his own
composition. See <er>Troubadour</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Vivacity and picturesquenees of the <qex>jongleur's</qex>
verse.</q> <rj><qau>J R. Green.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A juggler; a conjuror. See <er>Juggler</er>.</def>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj></p>

